Frog simulation:
a finite state space and a Marcov chain

Junkyu Park

max_iter <- 250
number_of_pads <- 20
state_space <- 1:number_of_pads
X <- NULL
X[1] <- state_space[number_of_pads] # initial state

i <- 2
while (i <= max_iter + 1) {
  choice <- floor(runif(1, min = 1, max = 4)) # choice ~ Unif{1, 2, 3}
  if (choice == 1) { # move left
    if (X[i - 1] == state_space[1]) {
      X[i] <- state_space[number_of_pads]
    } else {
      X[i] <- X[i - 1] - 1 
    }
  } else if (choice == 2) { # stays the same
    X[i] <- X[i - 1]
  } else { # move right
    if (X[i - 1] == state_space[number_of_pads]) {
      X[i] <- state_space[1]
    } else {
      X[i] <- X[i - 1] + 1
    }
  }
  i = i + 1
}

names(X) <- paste0("iter_", 0:max_iter)
print(X)

library(dplyr); library(tidyr); library(ggplot2)
state_df <- data_frame(
  iterations = rep(
    paste("Iteration", 0:max_iter), 
    each = number_of_pads
  ),
  state_space = rep(state_space, max_iter + 1), 
  # pads_point = rep(1:(max_iter + 1), each = number_of_pads)
  pads_point = rep(1, number_of_pads * (max_iter + 1))
)
comparison_df <- data_frame(state_space)
for (i in 1:(max_iter + 1)) {
  mutating_code <- paste0(
    "comparison_df <- comparison_df %>% ",
    "mutate(`Iteration ", i - 1, "` = state_space == X[i])"
  )
  eval(parse(text = mutating_code))
}
comparison_df <- comparison_df %>% gather(iterations, value, -state_space)

states_df <- state_df %>% 
left_join(
  comparison_df, by = c("state_space", "iterations")
) %>%
mutate(
  iterations = factor(
    iterations,
    levels = paste("Iteration", 0:max_iter)
  )
)

library(gganimate) # Version 1.0.0
anim <- ggplot(
  states_df, 
  aes(
    x = factor(state_space), y = pads_point, 
    color = value#, frame = iterations (not any more)
  )
) + 
  geom_point() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("black", "red")) +
  coord_polar(start = .15) +
  labs(title = "{closest_state}", x = "", y = "") +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  transition_states(
    iterations,
    transition_length = 3,
    state_length = 1
  ) +
  enter_drift() + exit_drift()
print(X)
